Head (
<figureCitation id="13142A49FFB7FFEAFEDFFA943E31F46A" box="[279,361,1292,1317]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) broader than long, punctate, base slightly concave. Temples shorter than eyes, with few squamous setae on upper part. Cephalic median groove weak or missing. Vertex, metarostrum and mesorostrum grooved. Sides of metarostrum (
<figureCitation id="13142A49FFB7FFEAFDC4FACC3D03F422" box="[524,603,1364,1389]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) glabrous. Prorostrum shorter than head, metarostrum and mesorostrum together, its length similar in both sexes. Venter of head and metarostrum with dull longitudinal median shallow groove, almost glabrous. Venter of mesorostrum with squamous setae. Antennal scape longer than antennomeres 2–3 together; articles 2–8 much broader than long, cylindrical; articles 3–8 with one row of raised setae; articles 9– 11 strongly laterally flattened in both sexes (
<figureCitation id="13142A49FFB7FFEAFD41FA7C3D84F4B2" box="[649,732,1508,1533]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036CCFFB7FFEAFF0FF9913CD3F7C3" blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" pageId="4">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13142A49FFB7FFEAFE82F99F3EC3F76E" box="[330,411,1543,1568]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) shiny, punctate, with prostrate fine setae; longitudinal median groove deeper at base, weakly connected to collar constriction. Metasternum with large punctures on sides; venter longitudinally grooved. Elytra glabrous, shiny, base straight to weakly concave, humeral calli not projecting forward; striae 3–10 strongly punctate. Femora unarmed, glabrous except few thick setae at base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036CCFFB7FFEAFF1BF90F3CF2F60E" blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" pageId="4">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13142A49FFB7FFEAFE9DF90F3EFEF7FE" box="[341,422,1687,1712]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) with sternites III–IV punctate (but without row of punctures at apex of sternite IV), longitudinally depressed; sternites V–VI with fine line of shallow setose punctures; sternite VII of male with several large punctures, almost smooth in female (
<figureCitation id="13142A49FFB7FFEAFD28F9473C6BF7B6" box="[736,819,1759,1784]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Tergite VIII of female strongly dentate, with apical median notch; epipleurites VIII with short spiculum; spermatheca: 
<figureCitation id="13142A49FFB7FFEAFC6EF89C3CA0F652" box="[934,1016,1796,1821]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
. Sternites VIII–IX of male: 
<figureCitation id="13142A49FFB7FFEAFA8EF89C3AC0F653" box="[1350,1432,1796,1821]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
. Tegmen with elongate, thin parameroid lobes (
<figureCitation id="13142A49FFB7FFEAFD69F8BF3DACF60E" box="[673,756,1831,1856]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Penis: 
<figureCitation id="13142A49FFB7FFEAFC9CF8BF3CFEF60E" box="[852,934,1831,1856]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[180,1388,203,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[170,1400,195,1877]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Stereodermus spp. 1 – 8, S. micropterus Mantilleri, sp. nov., ♀: 1, paratype, habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, head, lateral view; 4, left antenna; 5, abdomen; 6, abdominal tergum (mn, metanotum; hw, hind wing; TII, tergite II; TVI, tergite VI; TVII, tergite VII); 7, tergite VIII; 8, coxites and spermatheca. 9 – 18, S. platycornis Mantilleri, sp. nov.: 9, ♀ paratype, habitus; 10, head and prothorax, dorsal view; 11, head, lateral view; 12, right antenna; 13, ♂, abdomen; 14, ♀, sternite VII; 15, ♂, sternites VIII – IX; 16, tegmen; 17, penis; 18, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246756/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3356547FFB7FFEAFF0FF8D43BE8F62A" box="[199,1200,1868,1893]" pageId="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9036CCFFB7FFEAFF0FF8D43BE8F62A" blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" box="[199,1200,1868,1893]" pageId="4">
<emphasis id="B95BEADEFFB7FFEAFF0FF8D43E1EF62B" bold="true" box="[199,326,1868,1893]" pageId="4">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet refers to the strongly flattened articles 9–11 of antennae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3356547FFB7FFEAFF0FF8F73AD4F6BB" pageId="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9036CCFFB7FFEAFF0FF8F73AD4F6BB" blockId="4.[151,1437,932,2037]" pageId="4">
<emphasis id="B95BEADEFFB7FFEAFF0FF8F73E6CF6C6" bold="true" box="[199,308,1903,1928]" pageId="4">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D4FFFB7FFEAFE8BF8F73D39F6C6" box="[323,609,1903,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Stereodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platycornis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95BEADEFFB7FFEAFE8BF8F73D39F6C6" box="[323,609,1903,1928]" italics="true" pageId="4">Stereodermus platycornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26857A5FFB7FFEAFDA1F8F73D9DF6C6" box="[617,709,1903,1928]" pageId="4" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B95BEADEFFB7FFEAFDA1F8F73D9DF6C6" bold="true" box="[617,709,1903,1928]" pageId="4">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is easily differentiated from all other taxa of the genus: it is the sole known species with articles 9–11 of antennae flattened. Its affinities with other 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D4FFFB7FFEAFB91F80C3BA9F6E3" box="[1113,1265,1940,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Stereodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95BEADEFFB7FFEAFB91F80C3BA9F6E3" box="[1113,1265,1940,1965]" italics="true" pageId="4">Stereodermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unclear. In the key given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4B3DFFB7FFEAFEA5F8203DF2F69F" author="Mantilleri" box="[365,682,1976,2001]" pageId="4" refString="Mantilleri, A. &amp; Sforzi, A. (2006) Review of the Neotropical species of the genus Stereodermus Lacordaire, 1866 (Coleoptera: Brentidae: Stereodermini). Zootaxa, 1207, 3 - 64." type="journal article" year="2006">Mantilleri &amp; Sforzi (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, it is close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D4FFFB7FFEAFC95F8213BC6F69F" authority="Sharp, 1895" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1895" box="[861,1182,1976,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Stereodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticollis">
<emphasis id="B95BEADEFFB7FFEAFC95F8213B5AF69F" box="[861,1026,1976,2001]" italics="true" pageId="4">S. puncticollis</emphasis>
Sharp, 1895
</taxonomicName>
, known from 
<collectingRegion id="49EBF82EFFB7FFEAFA82F8203AC4F69F" box="[1354,1436,1976,2001]" country="Paraguay" name="Central" pageId="4">Central</collectingRegion>
America. Smaller size, shorter parameroid lobes and, above all, flattened antennomeres, separate the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
